-- IPIC First-Half Profit From Continuing Operations Drops to $159.2 Million
-- B y   C a m i l l a   H a l l   a n d   A r i f   S h a r i f
-- 2010-11-02T05:52:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-02/ipic-first-half-profit-from-continuing-operations-drops-to-159-2-million.html
International Petroleum Investment
Co., an Abu Dhabi government-backed investor, had a first-half
profit of $159.2 million from continuing operations compared
with $2.65 billion a year ago, according to its bond prospectus.  Profit from continuing operations in 2009 jumped to $3.86
billion from $305.5 million in the previous year, while revenue
rose to $9.92 billion from $9.85 billion, according to the
document. IPIC had assets of $48.2 billion at the end of June,
the prospectus said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camilla Hall in Dubai at 
